Victor DONATO, Jr., Plaintiff in Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. November 5, 1925.) No. 85. Bertram M. Manne, of Brooklyn, N. Y., for plaintiff in error. Ralph C. Greene, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Wm. A. De Groot, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for the United States.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MAN-TON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in open court.
